Package dev dependencies are now dependencies

* According to https://github.com/webpack/webpack/issues/520#issuecomment-331689542, all deps should reside in `dependencies`
* This also improves compatibility with the default behavior of `npm install x`
Updated lodash-es and "npm install" with npm 6.0.0

use the webpack build in plugin to handle env variables

Webpack has an build in plugin to handle process env variables https://webpack.js.org/plugins/environment-plugin/#usage-with-default-values . In my opinion this is a good documented way and makes the 'inline-environment-variables-webpack-plugin' obsolete. So this PR change the webpack config to use the  build in plugin and removes the 'inline-environment-variables-webpack-plugin'.

[npm] Bugfix: Downgraded "copy-webpack-plugin" to version 6.0.0 for now.

Version 6.0.1 and newer (including 6.1.0) do not process the "transform" option well. CSP-DIRECTIVES-PLACEHOLDER inside of "_headers" is not replaced well.

Make transform also work for copy-webpack-plugin 6.1.0.

If multiple patterns reference similar or identical files (e.g. "../public" and "../public/_headers") it is not well defined, which pattern will be executed - the first or the last? To avoid this confusion now "../public" is copied, but only "public/_headers" is transformed.

copy-webpack-plugin 6.0.1 most likely broke because of https://github.com/webpack-contrib/copy-webpack-plugin/pull/484.

Use "overrides" to help npm version 8.3 and newer.

> npm rm es-check && npm i es-check@^5.2.4

The "overrides" flag allows to make specific changes to (sub-)dependencies (see [1]). It is supported by npm 8.3 and newer (see [2]).

With this change after an "npm i" "npm audit" will print "found 0 vulnerabilities". Previously it printed "6 moderate severity vulnerabilities".

[1] https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/v8/configuring-npm/package-json#overrides
[2] https://github.com/npm/cli/releases/tag/v8.3.0
